usions and realities of security in all areas of transport and trade and illuminates many of the difficult ethical problems these extra-legal activities pose.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aInternational economic relations. 0aOrganized crime. 0aSmuggling. 0aTransnational crime. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  a21st century global economics.  a21st century global history.  aafrica.  aanthropology.  aarms.  aasia.  ablood diamonds.  acalifornia series in pubic anthropology.  acriminal activity.  adrugs.  aeconomic power.  aeconomic war zones.  aeconomy.  aeurope.  aexotica.  aextra legal activity.  afood.  aglobal crime.  aglobal disaster.  aglobalization.  aillegal trade.  ainternational.  amilitary takeovers.  aoil.  apharmaceuticals.  apower and wealth.  apower elite.  aprofiteers.  arobber barons.  asmugglers.  atrade.  atransnational.  aunited states.  avictims.  awar orphan.  awealth.  aworld economy.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052094063540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520940635423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520940635/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles